Here's a simple C++ program illustrating how to count the occurrences of a given target word from a text file, line by line:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>
#include <map>
#include <regex> // For regex operations

int main() {
    std::string filename = "example_textfile.txt";  // Replace with your desired input file name
    std::string targetWord = "specific";           // The keyword you want to search for

    std::smatch match;        // Object to hold the result of searching operations using regular expressions
    std::regex regexPattern(std::regex("(\\b)" + targetWord + "(\\b)", std::regex_constants::icase));
                             // Case-insensitive regex pattern to match the whole word 'targetWord'

    std::ifstream inputFile(filename);      // Create an ifstream object to read from the specified text file
    std::map<std::string, int> wordCounts; // A map to store unique words found and their respective counts

    if (!inputFile) {
        std::cerr << "Unable to open file '" << filename << "'" << std::endl;
        return -1;
    }

    std::string line;
    while (std::getline(inputFile, line)) {   // Read each line from the file
        for (std::sregex_iterator it(line.begin(), line.end(), regexPattern), end; it != end; ++it) {
            std::string matchedWord = it->str(); // Get the matched word from the iterator
            wordCounts[matchedWord]++;          // Increment the count of this unique word
        }
    }

    inputFile.close();                       // Close the file after reading is completed

    std::cout << "\nNumber of occurrences of \"" << targetWord << "\": " << ((wordCounts[targetWord]) ? wordCounts[targetWord] : 0) << '\n';
    return 0;
}
```

Before running the code, ensure to create a text file named `example_textfile.txt`. This example assumes the existence of such a file containing text data. Adjust the variable `filename` according to your chosen input file's name. Also, change the `targetWord` variable to the specific word you wish to find occurrences of within the text file. The program uses regular expressions for case-insensitive matching of entire words. It maintains a `wordCounts` map to keep track of the number of times each distinct word appears in the document. The final print statement shows the count of the specified target word.
